Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Thinly slice the @mushrooms{250%g}.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}(trimmed and sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste} in a large #pot on medium-high heat.

Add the mushrooms and carrots to the pot and fry until softened, ~{5-7%mins}.

Meanwhile, chop half the @potatoes{200%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add @paprika{1%sachet} and chopped potatoes to the pot and fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, 250ml @water{to taste} and @chopped tomatoes{1%pack}.

Simmer for ~{15-18%mins}.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Cheesy Crostini ==

While the stew simmers, cut the @baguette{2}(sliced into 2cm slices). Lay the slices onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Toast until golden brown, ~{8-10%mins}.

Sprinkle the @grated cheese{50%g} on top of the bread and return to the oven for ~{1-2%mins}, until the cheese has melted.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

== Finishing ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix together @flour{2%tbsp} and @water{1%tbsp}.

Add to the simmering stew and cook for another ~{3-5%mins}.

Season to taste with @sugar{to taste}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the stew between #bowls{} and serve with the cheese crostini on the side.

Garnish with sliced scallions. Tuck into your warm and hearty meal!